The Apple-OpenAI =E2=80=9CDeal=E2=80=9D
-----------------------

From Bloomberg ( https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-06-12/apple-t=
o-pay-openai-for-chatgpt-through-distribution-not-cash ) :

When Apple Inc. Chief Executive Officer Tim Cook and his top deputies this =
week unveiled a landmark arrangement with OpenAI to integrate ChatGPT into =
the iPhone, iPad and Mac, they were mum on the financial terms. Left unansw=
ered on Monday: which company is paying the other as part of a tight collab=
oration that has potentially lasting monetary benefits for both. But, accor=
ding to people briefed on the matter, the partnership isn=E2=80=99t expecte=
d to generate meaningful revenue for either party =E2=80=94 at least at the=
 outset.

The arrangement includes weaving ChatGPT, a digital assistant that responds=
 in plain terms to information requests, into Apple=E2=80=99s Siri and new =
writing tools. Apple isn=E2=80=99t paying OpenAI as part of the partnership=
, said the people, who asked not to be identified because the deal terms ar=
e private. Instead, Apple believes pushing OpenAI=E2=80=99s brand and techn=
ology to hundreds of millions of its devices is of equal or greater value t=
han monetary payments, these people said. Meanwhile, Apple, thanks to OpenA=
I, gets the benefit of offering an advanced chatbot to consumers =E2=80=94 =
potentially enticing users to spend more time on devices or even splash out=
 on upgrades.

The Article includes several other pertinent details, including:

* ChatGPT subscriptions currently sold via the OpenAI app do give Apple a c=
ut (obviously); there are not any details about whether or not there will b=
e a way for OpenAI to upsell from within the integration, but I would bet t=
here will be.
* The deal is not exclusive; a deal to offer Gemini as an option should be =
finished by the end of the year; Apple has also had talks with Anthropic.
* Apple does expect money to flow eventually, but in their direction; they =
see chatbots as a threat to the revenue they make from the Google search de=
al.

